thread.title: Man critically injured in 3-semi crash on I-90 offramp
thread.title_full: Man critically injured in 3-semi crash on I-90 offramp | The Seattle Times

author: Christine Clarridge
title: Man critically injured in 3-semi crash on I-90 offramp
text:
A man was taken to Harborview Medical Center in Seattle with critical injuries after he apparently drove his semitruck into two other semis on an offramp from Interstate 90 around 4:15 a.m. Wednesday.
Washington State Patrol spokesman Trooper Chris Webb said police think that two semis were parked on the shoulder of the Exit 34 offramp to North Bend when the third semi slammed into them.
The driver of the third semi, the moving vehicle, is the person who was hurt, he said.
As of 7 a.m., the exit remained closed, Webb said.
For current traffic information, go to wsdot.com .
